programme.title: Who Do You Think You Are? USA: Allison Janney
programme.desc: Award-winning stage, film and TV actress Allison Janney traces her family tree and uncovers a story that ties her to some of America's first British settlers. She learns that the family's journey to North America almost ended in tragedy

programme.title: Japan: Earth's Enchanted Islands: The Southwest Islands
programme.desc: In the south-west of Japan, the Ryukyu Islands stretch towards the tropics and all life on them is influenced by the power of the sea, with volcanos and typhoons forces to be reckoned with. Michelle Dockery narrates a journey beginning at an island at the top of the chain and travelling south, revealing unexpected stories of isolation, unique wildlife and unsolved mysteries

programme.title: Flog It!: Wiltshire 52
programme.desc: Paul Martin presents from Longleat in Wiltshire, where experts Claire Rawle and David Fletcher value items brought in for examination by members of the public, including an autograph album that evokes the glamour of bygone eras and a marble statuette that previously found use as a goal-post for backyard football practice. Paul also gets up close and personal with some of the region's most exotic residents as he relates the history of Longleat Safari Park

programme.title: Richard Osman's House of Games: Week 15: Wednesday

programme.title: Clive Myrie's African Adventure: Marrakech
programme.desc: In Morocco, Clive travels to Marrakesh, known around the world as the Red City for the red clay buildings that line its streets. He meets a Medina chef whose slow roasted lamb, cooked in underground ovens, has had the Royals of approval. In a souk, he masters the art of creating stunning tile mosaics, learns the skills required to make authentic Moroccan rugs, before spending the night in the High Atlas Mountains

programme.title: Rick Stein's Australia
programme.desc: The chef ends his journey of New South Wales on the south coast, known as the Sapphire Coast for its vibrant deep-blue waters. He explains why it's his favourite region in Australia, enjoys the seafood and looks toward the future

programme.title: Digging for Britain: Medieval Murder and Roman Pets
programme.desc: Featuring a vast first-century Roman compound, the warhorses that changed the course of history, a medieval murder mystery, the thriving farmstead belonging to Isaac Newton's mother, thousands of animal bones from a Roman farm, and a 300-million-year-old forest that built the modern world

programme.title: Reform: Ready to Rule?
programme.desc: With Reform UK consistently leading in the polls, Laura Kuenssberg examines the party's ambitions, organisation and efforts to professionalise. From its origins on the political fringes to representation on local councils and in Westminster, she asks whether Reform UK is ready to be a party of government. Featuring interviews with leading members of the party, the film explores how voter dissatisfaction is reshaping Britain's political landscape

programme.title: One Foot in the Grave: The Eternal Quadrangle
programme.desc: Victor takes up life drawing classes and Margaret is only too happy to see the back of him - until she learns the subject is a nude woman whom he has volunteered to drive home. Comedy, starring Richard Wilson and Annette Crosbie

programme.title: Mystery Road: Origin

programme.title: Amanda & Alan's Greek Job

Amanda forages for driftwood to turn into some bedside lamps and Alan leans into his rustic side, upcycling the old front doors into a statement headboard. Away from the project, Alan whisks Amanda away to a tourist hotspot known as the Channel of Love and onwards to the stunning clifftop Paleokastritsa Monastery, where the peaceful tranquillity of the surroundings prompts Amanda to reflect on a very poignant time in her life

programme.title: Dragons' Den

A London-based founder tips her hat to sustainability by reinventing pre-loved headwear as bespoke designer pieces, a charismatic entrepreneur hopes for investment into his business transforming smartphone memories into cherished keepsakes, two Leeds-based business partners showcase their plant-based drink powered by an east African super-crop and a former pharmacist steps into the ring with her women-only self-defence venture

It takes hardy animals and tough people with real ingenuity to survive in this ever-changing place. Michelle Dockery narrates

programme.title: Clive Myrie's African Adventure: Tangier
programme.desc: Clive concludes his journey by travelling to the northern tip of Morocco and meeting band the Master Musicians of Joujouka high in the Rif mountains. In a nearby farm, he grabs a bucket and helps milk goats to produce the smooth and creamy jben cheese. In the winding streets of Casablanca's old town, he learns new skills from a lantern-making artisan and meets a local fashion influencer to find the perfect Moroccan kaftan.

programme.sub-title: The Real Strictly Come Dancing: Access All Areas Season 1, Episode 1
programme.desc: Behind the scenes at the National Dance Championships as it celebrates its 50th anniversary. Cameras follow three couples from practice to performance, and hopefully to the podium. Professionals Petar Daskalov and Zia James are chasing the Latin trophy for a second year running. Eleven-year-old partners Leo and Chloe, who have been dancing together for just a year, are hoping to shine in both Latin and Ballroom. And after six attempts at the Amateur Ballroom Championships, Andrei Toader and Mia Linnik-Holden are back on the dance floor, hoping it's seventh time lucky

programme.title: Digging for Britain: A Cornish Legend and an Ancient Wishing Well
programme.sub-title: A Cornish Legend and an Ancient Wishing Well
programme.desc: Featuring a team of archaeologists looking for evidence that St Michael's Mount in Cornwall was the fabled trading hub of Ictis, as well as an analysis of 291 bodies from the long-lost Dominican friary of St Saviour's in Haverfordwest in Pembrokeshire. Plus, two incredibly rare Roman cavalry swords discovered at a metal-detecting rally in Willersey, near Cheltenham, a look at how 3D scanning and printing are transforming the study of fragile artefacts, and a wishing well of coins found at a complex promontory fort in Pembrokeshire

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: 44 women begin the very first training camp at the new 1 billion dollar Cowboys' facility, The Star. At the First Meeting, Kelli lays down the law and makes it clear that eight women will be sent home this summer.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: First, the ladies need to have the "classic look" of a Dallas Cowboys Cheerleader. Kelli's hair and make-up transformations are legendary. The ladies are also assessed through a new state of the art fitness test, "Styku".

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: Kelli media trains the rookie candidates to determine who best represents the DCC at press events. NBC news anchor, Meredith Land tests their on-camera interview skills.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: Personality is critical when representing the DCC brand. Kelli takes the women on location to see how they interact during a public appearance.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: Katy Perry's choreographer, Nick Florez, stops by to offer some performance advice to the ladies. A day that each cheerleader never forgets. The first time they wear the DCC uniform to pose for their cameo photos.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: The squad goes on an appearance to support pop music star, Demi Lovato. The ladies learn the entrance to the famed pre-game dance. It's a make or break moment. If a woman can't learn it quickly it might be her last night.

programme.title: Dallas Cowboys Cheerleaders: Making the Team
programme.desc: With two suspended vets, the team must re-block their formations for their Hall Of Fame performance. New vets step up as a new point of the triangle is named. The rookie candidates try to get their footing during this never seen before rehearsal.
